# Formatting

## After `raise`

Always insert a **blank line** after any `raise` statement (including multi-line) before the next logical statement or block.

```python
# Good
if not episode:
    raise NotFoundException(f"Episode with id {episode_id} not found")

file_obj = episode.image

# Good (multi-line raise)
if not downloaded:
    raise NotFoundException(
        f"Episode {episode_id} cover not found in storage"
    )

logger.info(...)
```

```python
# Bad (no blank line after raise)
if not episode:
    raise NotFoundException(f"Episode with id {episode_id} not found")
file_obj = episode.image
```

## After `return`

Always insert a **blank line** after any `return` statement (including multi-line) before the next logical statement or block (e.g. next `if`, next assignment, or end of block).

```python
# Good
if cached_path.exists():
    return self._build_cover_file_response(cached_path, file_obj)

cache_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

# Good (multi-line return)
return self.get_response_template(
    template_name="episodes_detail.html",
    context={"episode": episode},
)
```

```python
# Bad (no blank line after return)
if cached_path.exists():
    return self._build_cover_file_response(cached_path, file_obj)
cache_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
```
